issues.description: The template repository includes Main.java with references to the SealSaloon class (e.g., creating an instance and calling methods), but SealSaloon is not present in the template repository. This creates a compilation error in the template code, confusing students about the starting state and preventing them from running the provided Main class as a baseline for testing.
issues.suggested_fix: Comment out or remove the lines in Main.java that reference SealSaloon (lines 11-27) in the template repository to ensure the template compiles and runs without errors, allowing students to add SealSaloon as per the problem statement without initial confusion.
